function clean_column(col)
    return replace(strip(lowercase(col)), ['-' => '_', ' ' => '_'])
end
```

This function first strips any leading or trailing whitespaces with `strip`, then lowercases the string with `lowercase`, and finally replaces spaces (`' '`) and hyphens (`'-'`) with underscores (`'_'`) using `replace`. The result is a clean column name in lowercase with no spaces or hyphens.
